subject: Re: Cole's Funny Picture Book
msgSnippet: I think there is an error in the dictionary... the first occurance of in is translated differently from all the other words that start with in...  To fix
messageBody:
I think there is an error in the dictionary... the first occurance of
"in" is translated differently from all the other words that start
with "in..." To fix it, all you need to do is open
"QS_Dict_TextOnly.txt", go to about the middle of the file, and change
the line "IN an" to "IN in".

I'm going to fix it and upload a new zip to the files section.

Jeff

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, Paige Gabhart <pgabhart@a...> wrote:
> Jeff:
>
> Thanks for the information. I had managed to discoverer on my own that
> cntrl v would work. I also used Notepad rather than a word processor,
> and the program worked fine, except that I ended up doing a good bit of
> tweaking once I started reading the output. One peculiarity that
> occurred was that the word "in" was consistently transcribed as "un"
> (schwa folled by "n"). But the dictionary is correct, so there must
> have been some weird key stroke in the original.
>
>
> By the way, "Quikscript" and "Read's Alphabet" are not in the
dictionary.
>
[snip]
